description:
Modify SX1262.cs to receive unsolicited RX_PACKET from sim and raise DIO1 interrupt.

Currently SX1262.cs only sends requests and reads responses. Need background listener for push messages.

```csharp
// Add background receive loop (run in IHasOwnLife or similar)
private void StartReceiveLoop()
{
    Task.Run(async () => {
        while (connected)
        {
            var msg = await ReadMessage();
            if (msg == null) break;

            byte msgType = msg[0];
            if (msgType == 0x27)  // RX_PACKET
            {
                HandleRxPacket(msg);
            }
            else if (msgType == 0x28)  // RX_TIMEOUT
            {
                HandleRxTimeout();
            }
        }
    });
}

private void HandleRxPacket(byte[] msg)
{
    // Decode: skip type byte, read payload/rssi/snr
    // Store in FIFO buffer (rxBuffer)
    // Set IRQ status: RxDone bit (bit 1)
    irqStatus |= 0x0002;

    // Raise DIO1 if RxDone is unmasked
    if ((irqMask & 0x0002) != 0)
    {
        dio1.Set(true);  // GPIO high → firmware ISR fires
    }

    rxMode = false;  // exit RX mode
}

private void HandleRxTimeout()
{
    // Set IRQ status: Timeout bit (bit 9)
    irqStatus |= 0x0200;

    if ((irqMask & 0x0200) != 0)
    {
        dio1.Set(true);
    }

    rxMode = false;
}
```

The firmware ISR will call GetIrqStatus, see RxDone, call ReadBuffer to get the packet.
